 The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) has said it has arrested a Chadian Boko Haram drug supplier in Taraba State and a trans-border trafficker in Yobe State. It has also recovered 477grammes of cocaine and heroin in Kaduna State.
One of the suspects, Adama Uomar Issa, was arrested on Wednesday, March 31 in Jalingo, Taraba State with 21.70Kg of Tramadol 225mg and 250mg.
